## What to do

### 1. home_screen.dart — Remove 7-day auto-expire filter
In _loadAnnouncements() (around lines 283-314), remove the filter that excludes update announcements older than 7 days. Change:
```dart
final allActive = await SupabaseService.instance.getActiveAnnouncements();
final now = DateTime.now();
final announcements = allActive.where((a) {
  if (a.type == AnnouncementType.update) {
    return now.difference(a.createdAt).inDays < 7;
  }
  return true;
}).toList();
```
To simply:
```dart
final announcements = await SupabaseService.instance.getActiveAnnouncements();
```
Remove the `now` variable and the `.where()` filter. The rest of the method (notification logic, setState) stays the same but uses `announcements` directly.

Also remove the import for AnnouncementType if it becomes unused (check — it may still be used in _buildAnnouncementBanner). Actually, AnnouncementType IS used in _buildAnnouncementBanner (line 327: `announcement.type == AnnouncementType.update`), so keep the import.

### 2. supabase_service.dart — Auto-deactivate previous update on create
In createAnnouncement() (around lines 591-605), BEFORE inserting the new announcement, if the type is `update`, deactivate all existing active update announcements:

```dart
Future<void> createAnnouncement({
  required String senderId,
  required String title,
  required String message,
  required AnnouncementType type,
  String? link,
}) async {
  // If publishing a new update, deactivate all previous active updates
  if (type == AnnouncementType.update) {
    await SupabaseConfig.client
        .from('announcements')
        .update({'is_active': false})
        .eq('type', 'update')
        .eq('is_active', true);
  }
  await SupabaseConfig.client.from('announcements').insert({
    'sender_id': senderId,
    'title': title,
    'message': message,
    'type': type.name,
    'link': link,
  });
}
```

