## What to do

Add unit tests that verify the `_findPeriodSchedules` helper logic. Since `_findPeriodSchedules` is a private method on SupabaseService and depends on Supabase client calls, we need to test the LOGIC in isolation by extracting the algorithm into a testable form.

### Approach: Create a standalone test that replicates the period-finding algorithm

Since we can't easily mock SupabaseService (it's a singleton with real Supabase calls), test the period-finding algorithm as a pure function. Create the test file with a local copy of the algorithm:

```dart
// test/data/supabase_service_swap_test.dart
import 'package:flutter_test/flutter_test.dart';
import 'package:flutter_cleanapp/models/cleaning_schedule.dart';

/// Replicates the _findPeriodSchedules logic from SupabaseService
/// for unit testing purposes.
List<CleaningSchedule> findPeriodSchedules(
  List<CleaningSchedule> sortedSchedules,
  CleaningSchedule anchor,
) {
  final anchorIndex = sortedSchedules.indexWhere((s) => s.id == anchor.id);
  if (anchorIndex == -1) return [anchor];

  final userId = anchor.userId;
  final result = <CleaningSchedule>[anchor];

  // Walk backward
  for (var i = anchorIndex - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    if (sortedSchedules[i].userId != userId) break;
    final diff = sortedSchedules[i + 1]
        .date
        .difference(sortedSchedules[i].date)
        .inDays;
    if (diff > 1) break;
    result.insert(0, sortedSchedules[i]);
  }

  // Walk forward
  for (var i = anchorIndex + 1; i < sortedSchedules.length; i++) {
    if (sortedSchedules[i].userId != userId) break;
    final diff = sortedSchedules[i]
        .date
        .difference(sortedSchedules[i - 1].date)
        .inDays;
    if (diff > 1) break;
    result.add(sortedSchedules[i]);
  }

  return result;
}
```

